(16, 1, '2013-08-02 18:21:09', '2013-08-02 18:21:09', 'Being a Sunday, naturally I had a nice sleep in, followed by some scrambled egg on toast. This time was different though because the bread I was using was the type and everyday German would use. I''m talking about a kind of triangle shaped bread, with the constancy of cake! At the very least I can say it is strong tasted, but with a lot of butter it sorts it out. Anyway, after that excitement, I went on a walk around the cycle tracks (Im defo getting a bike after seeing the bike tracks!) which seem to span for literally hundreds of flat miles. I did see the small town of Hettstadt on my way which was notherplace I nearly lived in. I didnt see any difference in my small town and that one though, and I saved 30 Euros where I am ;) Along the way I took a few standard pics, one of which was a very hard to keep still dragonfly, enjoy the picture and I''ll get back on here tomorrow!<a style="color: #007ea6;" href="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/P1010382.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-14" alt="It took too long to get this picture." src="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/P1010382.jpg" width="330" height="241" /></a>', 'Sunday Stroll', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-02 18:21:09', '2013-08-02 18:21:09', '', 13, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=16', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(17, 1, '2013-06-22 18:24:23', '2013-06-22 18:24:23', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/P10103901.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-18" alt="Love this too much, hence the gigantic picture." src="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/P10103901.jpg" width="600" height="400" /></a>\r\nAs the title says, yes I bought a bike. (Which you''ll see at the end of this post of course! ) Before this, I planned on visiting the huuuuge, and it was, supermarket or Hypermarket as they call it here. Its called ''REAL'' which took over the walmarts here, and they sell everything you could every think of. I was going to do some shopping, until i saw the massive bike section , thus ending up buying a bike. It was like an asda in there, just 5 times bigger. I did notice the stupidly cheap alcohol section, which had massive cartes of anything, for such low cost. Got some desperado naturally, and cheap too.</p>\r\nAnyway, after riding the new bike home, which I think was a bargain, (because i was starting to have doubts at getting a bike after looking in the bike shops ) I then cooked up some currywurst, becuase its amazing. Anyway, at the moment i''m fixing my bike ready for a long ride tomorrow/ doing some washing (because i can multitask ).\r\n\r\nIt is a saturday, did you expect more interesting things?\r\n\r\nBye till tomorrow, where hopefully I''ll get some pics of my ride.', 'I bought a bike.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'i-bought-a-bike', '', '', '2013-08-02 19:58:06', '2013-08-02 19:58:06', '', 0, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=17', 0, 'post', '', 0),
