></p>', 'I''m Back!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-02 19:47:23', '2013-08-02 19:47:23', '', 20, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=26', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(22, 1, '2013-08-02 19:39:14', '2013-08-02 19:39:14', 'Still here! Its been a while since I last posted here, but at least any readers know i''m alive and well :D If you have noticed, I have changed the blog totally, goes for something a bit more simplistic and easier to read. Anyway, to give you an update of what I''ve been up to since your last read, its been almost 2 months since I arrived here. I am getting a little better at  Deutsch now, my lessons are doing me good. For instance (Funfzehn Guthaben fur Fonic mobil bitte) Is one I use too often when needing credit for my phone (its not cheap calling home).\r\n\r\nI''m really loving work now, getting a really good grip on how this industry runs in the real world, and not meaning like one of those ''group projects'' we did in second year. Like everyone helps you out no matter how busy they are or however many meetings they seem to have. Myself at the moment does not have many different things to be working on at the same time, but its picking up.\r\n\r\nI''m settled in now, and especially happy now I have my Blackberry Back! After having a nice swim in the sea with it, and getting it fixed for a cool 90 quid, it arrived this week and having the Internet on a phone has never been so good!\r\n\r\nMy landlady still does the old age trick of making me odd food and leaving it in my room for me, and likes replacing my washing up sponges at least 3 times a week aha. Little bit crazy.\r\n\r\nAnyway, it would be way too much effort to type a whole months worth of stuff. Here''s a nice picture of a postcard I sent home: ( My work place is the long building in the bottom left! )\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'I''m Back!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-02 19:39:14', '2013-08-02 19:39:14', '', 20, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=22', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(23, 1, '2013-08-02 19:43:19', '2013-08-02 19:43:19', 'Still here! Its been a while since I last posted here, but at least any readers know i''m alive and well :D If you have noticed, I have changed the blog totally, goes for something a bit more simplistic and easier to read. Anyway, to give you an update of what I''ve been up to since your last read, its been almost 2 months since I arrived here. I am getting a little better at  Deutsch now, my lessons are doing me good. For instance (Funfzehn Guthaben fur Fonic mobil bitte) Is one I use too often when needing credit for my phone (its not cheap calling home).\r\n\r\nI''m really loving work now, getting a really good grip on how this industry runs in the real world, and not meaning like one of those ''group projects'' we did in second year. Like everyone helps you out no matter how busy they are or however many meetings they seem to have. Myself at the moment does not have many different things to be working on at the same time, but its picking up.\r\n\r\nI''m settled in now, and especially happy now I have my Blackberry Back! After having a nice swim in the sea with it, and getting it fixed for a cool 90 quid, it arrived this week and having the Internet on a phone has never been so good!\r\n\r\nMy landlady still does the old age trick of making me odd food and leaving it in my room for me, and likes replacing my washing up sponges at least 3 times a week aha. Little bit crazy.\r\n\r\nAnyway, it would be way too much effort to type a whole months worth of stuff. Here''s a nice picture of a postcard I sent home: ( My work place is the long building in the bottom left! )\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"> <a href="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/IMG_000002551.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-21" alt="My postcard sent to home (I work in the long building in the bottom left)" src="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/IMG_000002551.jpg" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>', 'I''m Back!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-02 19:43:19', '2013-08-02 19:43:19', '', 20, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=23', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(27, 1, '2013-08-02 17:51:32', '2013-08-02 17:51:32', '<p>I would first like to mention that the reason for myself not posting to this blog on the first day was due to me underestimating the uselessness of bringing a UK sim card abroad without checking out what would happen first. Apparently my sim doesnt work abroad, so until now I had no means of reaching the rest of the world without being in mcdonalds (free wifi).&nbsp;</p> <p>Anyway, I arrived in Germany Half deaf due to flying twice on the way, which hurt my ears for 24 hours afterwards. This is definitely persuading me towards using the train the way home. My landlady was very nice, and drove me to a shop to get quick food supplies, not to mention the bedding and all kitchen equipment ready to use!</p> <p>Over the weekend I decided I had better check out the town itself before jumping straight in on monday. I remembered the google maps route into Wurzburg off the top of my head luckily, so getting there was easy, although finding out it was a whole 8KM to town was a shock! Took me an hour and 45 to walk. Something had to change. Thus, I rented a bike and biked home. I should also mention that while in town, I was very productive in buying a new simcard and other vital goods to survive.</p> <p>Sunday was a pointless day, although I had been warned already about the &nbsp;shops being closed on this day, I persisted anyway, resulting in my wondering around time with as little only as McDonalds open. i had a quick bite to eat, then took some pictures of the town. (Note: I will post them here very soon!)</p> <p>The town is a very beautiful place where every building has fancy carvings around the windows, with no ordanary plain building you see at home. The painted ceiling in the fortress chuuch is amazing!</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Down to work! I started monday around 10am very nervous, but settled in within the frist half an hour once i had been introduced to everyone, and found my workstation ready for me. They had given me a brand new system which has an SSD, Windows 8 and is dual screen! Computers like that make me want to work. The first day was mainly a run through of what Im would be doing, and getting my head around the workings of our system.&nbsp;</p> <p>This followed in the second day with more setting up, and a couple of tasks set for me! One of which i''m still working on, &nbsp;but i wont divulge because work should never be discussed out of the workplace!&nbsp;<img title="Smile" src="http://craighep.co.uk/blog/editors/tiny_mce_3_5_7/plugins/emotions/img/smiley-smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /></p> <p>We do perform this little exercise every morning however where all the developers stand in a circle and we through a ball to each other, then tell the group what we are currently working on and what we have done so far that day. Although very useful, I do struggle a little bit because 99% speak in german, and this results in me having to pick out words.&nbsp;</p> <p>Two final notes, I did finally buy some tea, which has made me much happier now, because coffee was killing me and tea is what a true Yorkshire person should always drink! The other point is why I am writing this blog now... Because I have internet! I bought a little USB stick that allows me to connect to the internet for a small fee every day, although my signal in my room is non existant so I am doing this outside at the moment (Thank god its like 30 degrees haha)</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Hold on for the pictures soon to be uploaded!</p> <p>Bye for today!</p', 'My First Few Days', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-02 17:51:32', '2013-08-02 17:51:32', '', 6, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=27', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(29, 1, '2013-08-02 17:54:49', '2013-08-02 17:54:49', 'To all my millions of readers, I apologize for leaving it a bit late since the last post, just that I have been a bit occupied over the last few days. Starting Wednesday, I managed to get into a badminton club, which starts at 8 till half 9 (Convienient too saying my german lessons will run from after work till then!). The session was awesome, as they''re all over the age of 25 ish, the''yre all amazing players, I could learn a trick or two from them. Becuase I obvisously had no racket, one of them kindly leant me their spare, which to say the least was an expensive racket. The only downside to badminton was the place it was held. Being 37 degrees outside, it meant inside a sports hall with no air conditioning, (madness) it was well over 40 in there, and after an hour of playing it was unbearable. Anyway, got home at 11, bed. Hence no post haha.\r\n\r\nNext day was the day I recieved my mini oven. Yes, I didnt even have an oven in my mini kitchen, so i went out and bought one. Thing was though, I sent it to be picked up from store, but chose the farthest away store by accident. After an hour bus after work, I got my hugggge box and bussed home. Again, home at 11, and straight to bed.\r\n\r\nToday however, because youre reading this post!, was the day I went to the Wurzbrug free music festival. Next to the river a set of three stages, a load of foods, and a load of beers was involved. I tried a pancake, although no fancy toppings for me, I''m simple like that. The last music set on stage was a band in tribute to ACDC which I thought was brilliant! Anyway, after hanging out there with a few work mates, I''m home. But saving the energy this time to post. I should also mention I tried a well talked about donner kebab, which was actual normal meat, and still tasted good! It does feel wierd eating one in daylight though..\r\n\r\nLooking at how work has been over the past few days, its been getting harder, but more satisfying. I have been assigned to start a project with a work mate for a brand new piece of the software, heavily involved in the seimans phone company and also related to Google a tiny bit ;)  . I will meet with the CEO of my employer soon, exciting stuff!\r\n\r\nOn one last note, I took out 20 euros today, yet forgot to take the cash. FOOL i was. Got to wait for the bank to see if there are any extra 20''s in the cash machine to see if it was taken back in, then hopefully get my money. I hope.\r\n\r\nByeeee for now.', 'A few days later...', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-02 17:54:49', '2013-08-02 17:54:49', '', 8, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=29', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(30, 1, '2013-08-02 17:56:29', '2013-08-02 17:56:29', '<p>Well to my surprise I managed to last a whole week in this new strange place! Work today had me guessing and struggling as some of the tasks got harder, but my workmates make that up by being really helpful :) . Anyway, its Friday night, and looks as if i''ll be sat in watching a film tonight because i''m so hardcore.</p> <p>At least its still sunny, although theres nothing to do. Thank god for the internet, I''d be dead without it. I also should mention that i managed to find some bacon in a shop today, meaning i could have a little bit of home. It was amazing as I always make it too, so the crispiness makes it taste perfect. Anyway, you''ll notice i''m super bored, hence the irrelevent post aha. Anyway, If I think of something more useful to post later, I''ll stick it on here.</p> <p>Guten Tag!</p>', 'My First Week Complete!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '9-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-02 17:56:29', '2013-08-02 17:56:29', '', 9, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=30', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(31, 1, '2013-08-02 17:57:54', '2013-08-02 17:57:54', '<p>I seem to have the hang of the buses now, so getting to work and back is a breeze now. I have chosen to start working at half 8 everyday, meaning i finish early ;) although work is really flexible and lets me move around my hours which i find great!</p> <p>Anyway, things are getting better; I am coming more comfortable with work, for which I am getting set tasks very often, and I also managed to find a way to get interent in my signal-hating bedroom. I bought a really long usb extension i can just chuck out of the window! Clever ayyy.&nbsp;</p> <p>Although I need to take more pictures before I add a full blown library to this blog, Theres a panarama shot I made just now, which hopefully is decent-ish quality. It should follow after this post later on.</p> <p>Oh! and I forgot to mention! My work has told me the possibiltiy of them paying for me to have German lessons, meaning I will actually be able to hold a conversation at some point in time. Be prepared for the German/ Yorkshire mixed accent!</p> <p>Thats all for now!</p>', 'Day Three.', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '10-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-02 17:57:54', '2013-08-02 17:57:54', '', 10, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=31', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(32, 1, '2013-08-02 17:58:49', '2013-08-02 17:58:49', '<p>So its the fourth day of working at my new home in Germany. I''m becoming much more independent now, thankfully because i''m actually remembered the stuff my work mates are teaching me :D . My boss was on the phone today and looks like the language lessons are gonna be ready for me soon too. Excited for that for sure!</p> <p>Anyway, learnt a couple new things about the old place today, the important one was about the tax they place on bottles and cans. You know they charge 5p a bag in Wales? well they do similar but charge much more and add it onto the bill if you buy either a bottle or can of something.&nbsp; More importantly, if you take it back to a shop after youve finished, they give you money back! explains why im always seeing the same old man looking homeless seraching through bins for cans.</p> <p>Oh and yes, I had to register myself today to make sure the people running the country know im here and working. To do this, i went down to the town hall, where after waiting for 50 minutes, was told i was in the wrong place! I was slightly annoyed, but the walk around the town in the sun made me feel much better. I''m gonna get unbelievebly tanned.</p> <p>One last thing, my landlady, which is the cleanest person ever, looks as if she''s been in my room today, emptied my bins, folded my bedding and even left me food! Yes with a note saying ''good apitite'', I was presented with a set of cold boiled potatoes, a strange sauce and a sasuage. Was a&nbsp;lovely thought, but i couldnt eat it haha. I did try a Bratwurst hot dog today in town though, THAT was amazing. Chow.</p>', 'Day Four.', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-02 17:58:49', '2013-08-02 17:58:49', '', 11, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=32', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(33, 1, '2013-08-02 17:59:31', '2013-08-02 17:59:31', '<p>I never thought i''d need a weekend to relax, but after getting up at 7 every morning this week it was well deserved. After getting up at half 10 (woooo), I met a workmate to see and try a few delights of Wurzburg. This started by firstly trying a new beer, which was heavy like Guiness, yet fruity. It was good. Also heard they do bananna versions too which sunds like something i''m gonna try in the future! I also had something called a Currywurst today, (Bascially a sasuage covered in ketchup, sprinkled with curry powder, served with chips) which was great, just rather large. I do reccomend it though if anyone ever gets over here!</p> <p>Anyway, after that, we grabbed the tram to the artifical beech at the side of the river, which was very odd, as they play carribean music and feels almost like being in anotehr country. I had a coctail, lounged on a deckchair and watched as some rather big boats went past. The weather although cloudy, as very warm, making the day much better!</p> <p>Also, I might not be active from 8pm onwards today until monday due to my internet stick-thing being stupidly confusing to add credit to. I mean, at home you just ring up and type in the voucher number, while with this thing you apparently text it and its done. I tried that twice, and had no reply, so I have no idea if its done or not!</p> <p>Bye for a while (maybe), I''ll keep you all updated as per! :)</p>', 'Weekends are so lonnng...', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '12-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-02 17:59:31', '2013-08-02 17:59:31', '', 12, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=33', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(34, 1, '2013-08-02 18:22:23', '2013-08-02 18:22:23', '<p style="text-align: center;">Being a Sunday, naturally I had a nice sleep in, followed by some scrambled egg on toast. This time was different though because the bread I was using was the type and everyday German would use. I''m talking about a kind of triangle shaped bread, with the constancy of cake! At the very least I can say it is strong tasted, but with a lot of butter it sorts it out. Anyway, after that excitement, I went on a walk around the cycle tracks (Im defo getting a bike after seeing the bike tracks!) which seem to span for literally hundreds of flat miles. I did see the small town of Hettstadt on my way which was notherplace I nearly lived in. I didnt see any difference in my small town and that one though, and I saved 30 Euros where I am ;) Along the way I took a few standard pics, one of which was a very hard to keep still dragonfly, enjoy the picture and I''ll get back on here tomorrow!<a style="color: #007ea6;" href="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/P1010382.jpg"><img class="wp-image-14 aligncenter" alt="It took too long to get this picture." src="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/P1010382.jpg" width="400" height="300" /></a></p>', 'Sunday Stroll', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-02 18:22:23', '2013-08-02 18:22:23', '', 13, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=34', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(35, 1, '2013-08-02 18:27:49', '2013-08-02 18:27:49', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/P10103901.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-18" alt="Love this too much, hence the gigantic picture." src="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/P10103901.jpg" width="600" height="400" /></a>\r\nAs the title says, yes I bought a bike. (Which you''ll see at the end of this post of course! ) Before this, I planned on visiting the huuuuge, and it was, supermarket or Hypermarket as they call it here. Its called ''REAL'' which took over the walmarts here, and they sell everything you could every think of. I was going to do some shopping, until i saw the massive bike section , thus ending up buying a bike. It was like an asda in there, just 5 times bigger. I did notice the stupidly cheap alcohol section, which had massive cartes of anything, for such low cost. Got some desperado naturally, and cheap too.</p>\r\nAnyway, after riding the new bike home, which I think was a bargain, (because i was starting to have doubts at getting a bike after looking in the bike shops ) I then cooked up some currywurst, becuase its amazing. Anyway, at the moment i''m fixing my bike ready for a long ride tomorrow/ doing some washing (because i can multitask ).\r\n\r\nIt is a saturday, did you expect more interesting things?\r\n\r\nBye till tomorrow, where hopefully I''ll get some pics of my ride.', 'I bought a bike.', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '17-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-02 18:27:49', '2013-08-02 18:27:49', '', 17, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=35', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(37, 1, '2013-08-03 14:21:35', '2013-08-03 14:21:35', '', 'Creeepy church thing', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1078903_10151740297993418_91197407_o', '', '', '2013-08-03 14:21:35', '2013-08-03 14:21:35', '', 36, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/1078903_10151740297993418_91197407_o.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(38, 1, '2013-08-03 14:22:00', '2013-08-03 14:22:00', 'Being a Saturday, my favourite day of the week (Sundays just make me think of the impending work on the next day ;) ) I decided to bike into town, via  a new way. This way avoidided the usual cycle route because when its this warm milllions and millions of flies love to hang there and hit you in the face. Anyway, This route took me past the creepy looking lonely church place on top of a hill in the middle of a wheat field. This looks like one of them places you either get secretly married in or just plain horror movie settings. Anyway, here it is:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Day out on the bike', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '36-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-03 14:22:00', '2013-08-03 14:22:00', '', 36, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=38', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(40, 1, '2013-08-02 17:40:13', '2013-08-02 17:40:13', '', 'Wurzburg', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-02 17:40:13', '2013-08-02 17:40:13', '', 2, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=40', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(39, 1, '2013-08-03 14:27:21', '2013-08-03 14:27:21', 'Being a Saturday, my favourite day of the week (Sundays just make me think of the impending work on the next day ;) ) I decided to bike into town, via  a new way. This way avoidided the usual cycle route because when its this warm milllions and millions of flies love to hang there and hit you in the face. Anyway, This route took me past the creepy looking lonely church place on top of a hill in the middle of a wheat field. This looks like one of them places you either get secretly married in or just plain horror movie settings. Anyway, here it is:\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/1078903_10151740297993418_91197407_o.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-37" alt="Creeepy church thing" src="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/1078903_10151740297993418_91197407_o.jpg" width="600" height="500" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">So upon arriving in town, the sun came out, and did it. I did my usual stunts of hiding in the shade, finding shops with air conditioning and consuming various different fizzy drinks. Who knew finding shorts could be so difficult for a man? Like H&amp;M usually have a mans section right? well not here. So after just getting more mobile credit, I decided to cycle home, when it started raining. This was good though, as it kept me nice and cool up the hill on the way home. Just before I got back I did almost have a collision with a car though! An idiot in an Audi decided to cut my up without indicating, making me almost hit him straight in the side. Cheers brakes.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Anyway, the rest of today will just involve hiding in my cool room, watching films and eating German food stuff.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">I''ll keep posting!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>', 'Day out on the bike', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '36-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-03 14:27:21', '2013-08-03 14:27:21', '', 36, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=39', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(41, 1, '2013-08-03 14:27:36', '2013-08-03 14:27:36', 'Being a Saturday, my favourite day of the week (Sundays just make me think of the impending work on the next day ;) ) I decided to bike into town, via  a new way. This way avoided the usual cycle route because when its this warm millions and millions of flies love to hang there and hit you in the face. Anyway, This route took me past the creepy looking lonely church place on top of a hill in the middle of a wheat field. This looks like one of them places you either get secretly married in or just plain horror movie settings. Anyway, here it is:\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/1078903_10151740297993418_91197407_o.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-37" alt="Creeepy church thing" src="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/1078903_10151740297993418_91197407_o.jpg" width="600" height="500" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">So upon arriving in town, the sun came out, and did it. I did my usual stunts of hiding in the shade, finding shops with air conditioning and consuming various different fizzy drinks. Who knew finding shorts could be so difficult for a man? Like H&amp;M usually have a mans section right? well not here. So after just getting more mobile credit, I decided to cycle home, when it started raining. This was good though, as it kept me nice and cool up the hill on the way home. Just before I got back I did almost have a collision with a car though! An idiot in an Audi decided to cut my up without indicating, making me almost hit him straight in the side. Cheers brakes.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Anyway, the rest of today will just involve hiding in my cool room, watching films and eating German food stuff.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">I''ll keep posting!</p>', 'Day out on the bike', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '36-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-03 14:27:36', '2013-08-03 14:27:36', '', 36, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=41', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(45, 1, '2013-08-04 17:28:39', '2013-08-04 17:28:39', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/P1010463.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-44" alt="The ramp to hell" src="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/P1010463.jpg" width="600" height="450" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">This fun looking ramp is something I go past time to time whilst riding around my area, and I finally though I should put it up on here. This is part of a crazy looking man made set of ramps on one of the bike routes, and this is by far the most steep, scariest and death defying ramp I have seen. I now know one thing I won''t be attempting while i''m here.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Anyway, naturally being a Sunday, this has comprised of a late get up time, doing whatever house work I needed to do and eating. I should also say that over the past 10 weeks I have been here, I seem to have collected up quite a bit of spare change. What happens here is that because I refuse to use a coin lesser than 50 cents when spending, it all gets thrown in a bowl waiting to be taken to the bank one day. I have already hit 35 Euros since I got here in change! And because I''m a little sad I worked out how much I could have when I leave.... 210 Euros! Nice money earner that.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Lastly, a bit more technically, I wrote a little Java sorting program today, seeing a video on the Computer science FB page yesterday made me want to create a program that read in as many random numbers as you want, and then tried out 9 different sorting algorithms (Insertion, Shell, Bubble, Bucket, Heap, Merge, Quick, Radix and Bogo*) and see which work fastest etc. I think Heap is my new favourite anyway.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Oh, heres a link to the zip in case you want to try it:</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Sorts.zip">Sorts</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">*Bogosort is pathetic.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>', 'The ramp to hell, and a little bit of Java', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-ramp-to-hell-and-a-little-bit-of-java', '', '', '2013-08-04 17:31:55', '2013-08-04 17:31:55', '', 0, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=45', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(46, 1, '2013-08-04 17:27:33', '2013-08-04 17:27:33', '', 'Sorts', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'sorts', '', '', '2013-08-04 17:27:33', '2013-08-04 17:27:33', '', 45, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Sorts.zip', 0, 'attachment', 'application/zip', 0),
