(59, 1, '2013-08-07 19:16:53', '2013-08-07 19:16:53', 'Today was the last day at work for the previous industrial year student at my workplace, after starting last June. Although I have gotten used to living and attempting to understand a completely different nationality, having someone in the office to speak a bit of English with was always nice :) Anyhow, I wish him the best luck being back in Aber for his final two years, and I''ll be there to join him next year. On the other hand of all this, I reckon that having solely German people to communicate with as my only option will force me a little bit more into speaking German. This, together with my 3/4 lessons a week i''m having at the moment will hopefully sharpen my skills!\r\n\r\nTonight I plan to salvage the files from my external hard drive which got kinda broken from being thrown around a bit at Uni, but I have managed to get it out of the case and use it as an internal one so getting the files off is pretty easy now :) I should mention why I dint blog yesterday, mainly being that after work then badminton, I was too tired even to turn on my computer. Even if there was a humongous thunderstorm I still slept like a log.\r\n\r\nSince this post is starting to slowly turn generic, I''ll be off now. Back tomorrow! ish.\r\n\r\n<em>P.s. It was great meeting you Chris! (Previous Industrial year guy) Thanks for all the help getting my on track ;)</em>', 'The lonely Englishman', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-lonely-englishman', '', '', '2013-08-07 19:18:34', '2013-08-07 19:18:34', '', 0, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=59', 0, 'post', '', 0),
