(68, 1, '2013-08-09 21:53:49', '2013-08-09 21:53:49', 'Okay, so as the title says today there was a minor flood today within my room while I was at work. I cam home after my German lesson to find all my items and chairs upon my bed and everything moved away from any walls. Turns out my Landlady had mopped up quite a bit of water from the floor due to me leaving my window open during quite a bit of rain. She is always telling me to leave it open, so the one time I do, this happens. Not again. Anyway, resulting this is the total re-movement of my furniture which seems to give me soo much more space. And its now spotless as if you could eat food off the walls.\r\n\r\nWork was very quite today with quite a few people out on holiday or working from home, so the tasks weren''t exactly flooding in. Nevertheless, Monday will be even quieter because the only other guy in my office room will also be out, so I will be in charge of a one man team (me) for that whole day!\r\n\r\nFinally, as tomorrow will be one of those too warm to go outside days, I plan to mess with computer hardware stuffff, and try get this hard drive fixed up.\r\n\r\nBack tomorrow!', 'The Great Flood... of my room', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '67-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-09 21:53:49', '2013-08-09 21:53:49', '', 67, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=68', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(71, 1, '2013-08-24 17:35:26', '2013-08-24 17:35:26', 'I don''t know if i''m saying welcome back to you, the reader, or me because of my long time gap since the last post. Either way, since you''re reading this it means I''m still surviving in Deutschland, and that my work people still like me :D Its still HOT here, except for a couple days of rain that was here a couple of weeks ago. And when it rains, it rains. Like the thunder here still scares me to death when it begins, especially if you have to walk through it.\r\n\r\nAnyway, jumping straight into the present, my new PC I intended/ starting planning for last Monday was completed on Thursday (Pretty fast ey?) and I did it from scratch, every piece bought separately. More amazing is that it actually works. So gaming is another possibility to add to my slightly boring weekends.\r\n\r\nI managed to find English brands this week in a shop in Wurzburg, kinda like M&amp;S in style but they have all the Mexican and Indian food i would ever need. Tad expensive though, but worth it. And whats more Is this week the square where I work had a min countries festival which meant a different set of stalls for each country all serving food. Wouldnt you know it, there was a British one, with a lovely big picture of Brighton pier stuck in the back of the stall. Naturally I bought a bag of Fudge which no one over here has heard of, and had a chat to the owner, who sounded off Eastenders. It was weird at least when someone else asked him something in German and then he sounded totally German replying. Wish I could do that now :P Soon I guess...\r\n\r\nAnyway, Chow for now!', 'Welcome back', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'welcome-back', '', '', '2013-08-24 17:35:26', '2013-08-24 17:35:26', '', 0, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=71', 0, 'post', '', 0),
