(75, 1, '2013-08-28 17:10:04', '2013-08-28 17:10:04', 'Bit confused by the name? Well not as confused as I was when my landlady gave me this strange tub of fruit she got from the garden. If i were to describe these in my best efforts, they are basically grapes that are bigger, and as solid as rocks. I''m yet to try one, but maybe later. I have Oreos for now ;) Anyway, work is going really well at the moment, having my project ongoing being the lead developer and all wooo! Its a bit quiet in the office at the minute though with a few people being lucky on holiday. I''m used to the routine of it all now too, getting up everyday at half 7 is fine on me now :)\r\n\r\nI should also mention that the weather is just cool enough to be able to live in now, and that the pesky Mosquitos have begun  to die out. They WERE annoying. This weeks task though: to find a hairdressers/ barbers and get the hair cut as normal as possible. Will be a challenge, but i bet my landlady could probably do it, she does stuff like that for work I think. Anyway, bye for now!\r\n\r\np.s. I have added the functionality on this blog to be able to subscribe for email updates when I post so you don''t have to check everyday or whatever now. Check the form below. If it doesn''t work or show, then give me a message and I''ll add you manually.\r\n\r\n[subscribe2]', 'The un-forbidden fruit', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-un-forbidden-fruit', '', '', '2013-08-28 17:16:14', '2013-08-28 17:16:14', '', 0, 'http://www.craighep.co.uk/blog/?p=75', 0, 'post', '', 0),
